WEBVTT

00:07.173 --> 00:12.262
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

00:16.766 --> 00:19.185
I know you don't want
to be here.

00:19.269 --> 00:21.813
But without you and Baruch,
I might never have found her.

00:22.313 --> 00:23.398
So, thank you.

00:24.816 --> 00:28.403
Nearly 400 years with Baruch
must have mellowed me.

00:28.987 --> 00:30.405
Four hundred years?

00:31.364 --> 00:33.533
-You know where he is now?
-Of course.

00:37.162 --> 00:39.205
Angels can connect to any mind,

00:39.289 --> 00:42.041
but between us,
the bond is even stronger.

00:45.170 --> 00:48.089
We feel as one,
though we are two.

00:56.264 --> 00:58.558
He's close to Asriel now.

01:00.685 --> 01:03.354
You know what Asriel
is going to ask of you.

01:05.023 --> 01:07.525
My father told me
about the war before he died.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.278
He told me I have a duty.

01:10.361 --> 01:12.447
BALTHAMOS:
There is a warrior in you, Will.

01:12.530 --> 01:15.116
You overpowered
the King of the Bears.

01:15.200 --> 01:18.870
And you'll find a way
to protect the one you love.

01:25.335 --> 01:29.214
(FIRE CRACKLES)

01:45.897 --> 01:51.653
♪ (CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:03.414 --> 02:05.083
(WATER LAPPING)

02:23.059 --> 02:24.102
ROGER PARSLOW: Lyra.

02:25.770 --> 02:28.731
(PANTS)

02:28.815 --> 02:33.194
-ROGER PARSLOW: Lyra.
-Roger! (PANTS)

02:33.278 --> 02:34.821
ROGER: You have to help me.

02:36.531 --> 02:37.657
LYRA BELACQUA: I will.

02:39.784 --> 02:41.786
I promise I won't let you down.

02:42.954 --> 02:46.082
-ROGER: They're hurting me.
-Who?

02:49.836 --> 02:52.922
Just tell me where you are
and I'll find you.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.632
ROGER: The Land of the Dead.

02:56.676 --> 03:00.221
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:06.352 --> 03:09.022
Roger!

03:11.608 --> 03:14.652
Roger!

03:16.321 --> 03:19.407
Roger!

03:19.490 --> 03:21.910
(GASPS) Roger.

03:21.993 --> 03:24.662
-(PAN SQUEAKS)
-♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:26.331 --> 03:28.207
I was having that dream again.

03:30.793 --> 03:33.296
We need to find him
when we get out of here.

03:33.379 --> 03:36.257
PAN: Where did you go? I...

03:38.009 --> 03:40.178
I couldn't follow you there.

03:40.261 --> 03:43.056
-The Land of the Dead.
-♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC SWELLS) ♪

03:43.139 --> 03:45.934
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:13.479 --> 05:16.649
♪ (THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

05:19.152 --> 05:21.946
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:22.030 --> 05:24.323
COMMANDER OGUNWE: Ah,
this is a decent set up.

05:24.407 --> 05:27.243
LORD ASRIEL BELACQUA:
Just a start, Commander.
Just a start.

05:27.326 --> 05:31.289
-(JEEP ENGINE REVS)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:31.372 --> 05:33.499
OGUNWE: It's very impressive,
Lord Asriel.

05:33.583 --> 05:36.836
But your soldiers, well, now,
they all need some structure.

05:36.919 --> 05:38.838
(CHUCKLES)
That's why you're here.

05:38.921 --> 05:40.798
Ruta, welcome back.

05:40.882 --> 05:43.760
Commander Ogunwe, allow me
to introduce Queen Ruta Skadi

05:43.843 --> 05:47.221
of the Lake Lubana witch clan
and her daemon, Sergi.

05:47.305 --> 05:49.766
She's a vital member
of my Council.

05:49.849 --> 05:52.602
-Commander.
-Your Majesty.

05:52.685 --> 05:54.020
LORD ASRIEL:
Ruta, if you wouldn't mind?

05:54.103 --> 05:57.273
You're well known to Ruta,
Commander. She chose you.

05:57.356 --> 05:58.733
-Chose me?
-LORD ASRIEL: Mm-hmm.

05:58.816 --> 06:01.486
I listen to whispers
between worlds.

06:01.569 --> 06:05.364
I hear things others do not.
We're assembling an army.

06:05.448 --> 06:08.743
You and your resistance soldiers
are some of the best.

06:08.826 --> 06:10.203
I'm glad you approve.

06:10.286 --> 06:12.997
We hope we can live up
to our reputation.

06:13.081 --> 06:14.290
We all hope that.

06:18.836 --> 06:20.505
How much more will we need?

06:20.588 --> 06:25.843
-Of what?
-This. Soldiers. Witches.

06:27.053 --> 06:29.847
It's the Authority's strength
that lies in numbers.

06:29.931 --> 06:31.849
Sheer wealth of people
willing to defend

06:31.933 --> 06:34.227
his mysticism and dogma.

06:34.310 --> 06:36.354
We just need enough
to provoke him.

06:38.898 --> 06:42.777
So all this
is just a provocation?

06:42.860 --> 06:44.737
(CHUCKLES) Come. You'll see.

06:50.201 --> 06:52.411
Find me the latest plans
for the Intention Craft.

06:52.495 --> 06:54.122
-CREW MEMBER: Yes, sir.
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

06:54.205 --> 06:56.040
How do you know
this one won't kill you?

06:56.124 --> 06:58.668
It would take more
than a little crash

06:58.751 --> 07:00.920
to put an end
to the pair of us.

07:01.003 --> 07:02.505
Commander, you asked

07:02.588 --> 07:04.590
how many soldiers
we were going to need.

07:04.674 --> 07:07.051
The truth is, I don't know.

07:07.135 --> 07:09.679
But the key
to provoking the Authority

07:09.762 --> 07:14.350
lies not in men,
it may well lie in Dust.

07:14.433 --> 07:18.312
Asriel, you talk in riddles,
I deal in strategy.

07:18.396 --> 07:19.981
I'm not being clear.
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

07:20.064 --> 07:22.817
We have to force the Authority
to show his face.

07:22.900 --> 07:26.279
And then, then we're going
to need all the fighters

07:26.362 --> 07:27.864
we can get our hands on.

07:28.406 --> 07:29.407
(CLICKS TONGUE)

07:30.700 --> 07:33.703
♪ (GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

08:41.854 --> 08:43.064
-(GASPS)
-(GUN COCKS)

08:43.147 --> 08:45.441
-♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-I didn't mean to scare you.

08:46.150 --> 08:47.693
What do you want?

08:47.777 --> 08:50.696
I don't mean you any harm.
I'm-- I'm looking for someone.

08:50.780 --> 08:53.491
A girl. Her name is Lyra.

08:53.574 --> 08:55.076
JOSEPH BLAKELY:
Were you followed?

08:55.910 --> 08:56.911
I don't think so.

08:56.994 --> 08:58.704
JOSEPH: Temple soldiers
are in the woods.

08:59.705 --> 09:00.915
I haven't seen anyone.

09:06.170 --> 09:07.922
Something happened here

09:08.005 --> 09:10.132
a few days ago,
and now they're everywhere.

09:10.216 --> 09:13.094
(DRONE WHIRRING)

09:14.095 --> 09:15.137
Come with us.

09:15.221 --> 09:20.351
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:24.814 --> 09:28.484
(DRONE WHIRRING)

09:35.908 --> 09:37.159
It's moving away.

09:40.454 --> 09:43.833
-♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
-(BIRDS CHIRPING)

09:43.916 --> 09:46.043
♪ (MILD TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

10:07.023 --> 10:10.609
It's the salt.
It burns the roots.

10:15.156 --> 10:16.574
...and these
to the southern garrison.

10:16.657 --> 10:19.493
-(WINGS FLUTTER)
-And 250 to the western...

10:19.577 --> 10:22.163
-ROKE: Lord Asriel.
-Roke.

10:23.080 --> 10:24.874
-No people.
-COMMANDER: Sir.

10:30.087 --> 10:31.922
-What is it?
-ROKE: A message

10:32.006 --> 10:34.550
from our Magisterium spy,
Agent Salmakia.

10:34.633 --> 10:37.720
She says they are preparing
to undertake a search mission.

10:37.803 --> 10:40.139
-For what?
-Your daughter, sir.

10:40.222 --> 10:42.058
They think she's
the most important child

10:42.141 --> 10:43.225
-that's ever lived.
-(SIGHS)

10:43.309 --> 10:45.394
Salmakia believes
she's in danger.

10:45.478 --> 10:47.730
When is Lyra not in danger?

10:49.106 --> 10:51.025
Anything else?

10:51.108 --> 10:54.862
-No. There's nothing else.
-LORD ASRIEL: Very good.

10:55.946 --> 10:58.282
(WINGS FLUTTER)

10:58.366 --> 11:00.493
STELMARIA:
You dismiss Lyra too easily.

11:01.952 --> 11:05.081
You know what the Magisterium
believe about her.

11:05.164 --> 11:08.084
According to the Authority,
Eve was the mother of creation.

11:08.167 --> 11:11.545
Lyra is simply the creation
of Marisa and I.

11:11.629 --> 11:13.506
She's not Eve,
she's a little girl.

11:13.589 --> 11:17.927
She must have some information
they need or some skill

11:18.010 --> 11:19.762
we've overlooked.

11:19.845 --> 11:22.139
Other than being able
to read the alethiometer,

11:22.223 --> 11:25.559
she has very little, I'm afraid.
Other than a nose for trouble.

11:25.643 --> 11:27.812
-(ROARS)
-LORD ASRIEL: What?

11:27.895 --> 11:30.940
-What would you like me to say?
-STELMARIA: The truth.

11:34.652 --> 11:36.362
There are angels above the camp.

11:36.445 --> 11:39.448
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(LORD ASRIEL GRUNTING)

11:39.532 --> 11:42.118
♪ (EPIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:43.285 --> 11:44.787
OGUNWE: What are they doing?

11:44.870 --> 11:47.581
(ANGELS WHOOSHING)

11:47.665 --> 11:49.083
LORD ASRIEL: They're fighting.

11:49.166 --> 11:53.921
(AIR WHOOSHES)

11:55.423 --> 11:57.883
-(GUN COCKING)
-Clear the camp!

11:57.967 --> 11:59.051
(INDISTINCT CLAMOR)

12:02.054 --> 12:05.266
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:09.562 --> 12:11.147
Not too close. Not too close.

12:11.230 --> 12:14.150
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

12:19.655 --> 12:20.906
Back away. Back away.

12:22.074 --> 12:23.242
His chest is moving.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.287
Let's say, one of them fights
for the Authority

12:26.370 --> 12:29.123
-and one for us, which is which?
-OGUNWE: I don't know.

12:29.206 --> 12:30.207
Maybe neither.

12:32.251 --> 12:34.044
Ruta?

12:34.128 --> 12:37.256
This one's higher status.
Could be an archangel.

12:37.882 --> 12:40.134
This one, I don't know.

12:40.217 --> 12:41.927
Shall we see if we can move him?

12:42.011 --> 12:43.637
LORD ASRIEL: Mm-hmm.

12:43.721 --> 12:45.556
-You have him?
-SOLDIER: Yes, sir.

12:50.728 --> 12:52.980
-(BARUCH GROANS)
-OGUNWE: Get back.

12:53.772 --> 12:55.024
(BARUCH GROANS)

12:56.150 --> 12:58.777
ASRIEL: Are you an agent
of the Authority?

12:58.861 --> 13:01.155
-(BREATHES HEAVILY) Please.
-Say again?

13:02.406 --> 13:04.742
There is a message
I must give to you.

13:08.454 --> 13:10.581
We're going to assume
that one's with the Authority

13:10.664 --> 13:11.916
and this one with us.

13:12.750 --> 13:15.461
I'll take him inside. Sergeant.

13:15.544 --> 13:17.588
Take him to
the intercision field chamber.

13:17.671 --> 13:19.089
All right. Give me your message.

13:20.257 --> 13:21.383
BARUCH: We found the boy.

13:22.092 --> 13:23.511
The bearer.

13:23.594 --> 13:25.387
ASRIEL: What boy?
What does he bear?

13:25.471 --> 13:27.223
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

13:27.306 --> 13:29.391
AEsahaettr. The God killer.

13:31.101 --> 13:33.312
The only weapon
that will destroy him.

13:34.813 --> 13:37.399
-Destroy who?
-The Authority.

13:38.984 --> 13:40.110
ASRIEL: What?

13:40.194 --> 13:43.197
(BREATHES SHAKILY)
And his Regent.

13:45.407 --> 13:46.450
My brother, Enoch.

13:49.703 --> 13:51.163
The Authority has a Regent?

13:52.039 --> 13:53.123
Baruch!

13:54.166 --> 13:56.877
How? Who did this?

13:58.629 --> 14:01.382
-An angel.
-We've already incarcerated him.

14:04.510 --> 14:05.719
He's leaving us.

14:07.221 --> 14:10.182
Not yet. Tell me
where I can find the boy.

14:13.435 --> 14:15.062
He's on his way to Lyra.

14:17.273 --> 14:18.274
Lyra?

14:20.651 --> 14:21.694
Find him.

14:23.070 --> 14:24.655
There is an angel waiting.

14:26.824 --> 14:28.659
(INHALES) My Balthamos.

14:32.121 --> 14:33.163
Find them.

14:34.540 --> 14:35.666
Find the knife.

14:43.882 --> 14:44.925
Balthamos.

14:49.388 --> 14:51.348
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

14:51.432 --> 14:55.227
-BALTHAMOS: Baruch!
-♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:01.317 --> 15:04.111
I don't understand.
It doesn't make sense.

15:04.194 --> 15:05.571
What doesn't make sense?

15:06.947 --> 15:08.490
What did they do to him?

15:09.575 --> 15:10.868
What happened, Balthamos?

15:12.911 --> 15:14.622
This is your fault.

15:15.372 --> 15:16.915
You forced me to come here.

15:16.999 --> 15:21.086
I wanted us to stay together.
I wanted to go with him.

15:22.004 --> 15:23.672
They've killed him!

15:29.762 --> 15:32.181
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

15:36.101 --> 15:38.020
(WINGS FLUTTERING)

15:46.528 --> 15:47.863
(WINGED CREATURES SCREECH)

16:02.336 --> 16:03.962
Messenger returns.

16:07.174 --> 16:08.300
(GUN COCKS)

16:13.389 --> 16:14.890
OGUNWE: He did not resist.

16:15.766 --> 16:17.351
Didn't say a word. He just...

16:18.519 --> 16:19.645
stared at me.

16:20.979 --> 16:24.525
Yesterday I believed
that angels were merely symbols

16:24.608 --> 16:29.405
and witches were villains
in children's stories.

16:30.322 --> 16:32.324
Yet, here I am.

16:37.287 --> 16:39.039
There you are.

16:39.123 --> 16:41.875
Our kind have been
to your world before.

16:41.959 --> 16:44.294
Many centuries ago.

16:44.378 --> 16:48.173
The Temple would burn women
they suspected of witchcraft.

16:48.757 --> 16:49.883
I remember it.

16:50.884 --> 16:53.804
Witches live
for many hundreds of years.

16:53.887 --> 16:55.514
Angels for millennia.

16:57.224 --> 17:00.394
It gives them
a power and perspective

17:00.477 --> 17:03.021
far greater than either
of our comprehension.

17:04.481 --> 17:06.400
I imagine they regard us witches

17:06.483 --> 17:08.902
in a similar way
as we see humans.

17:09.820 --> 17:10.988
And how is that?

17:11.071 --> 17:13.574
Your lives are short
and easily extinguished.

17:15.534 --> 17:17.411
So then why do you fight
with us?

17:18.454 --> 17:19.455
Hope.

17:21.498 --> 17:24.293
I believe there is a chance
we can win.

17:24.376 --> 17:27.671
And so, do you trust Asriel?

17:29.173 --> 17:31.091
RUTA SKADI:
I'd stake my life on it.

17:37.431 --> 17:44.229
(DOOR SQUEAKS, CLOSES)

17:44.313 --> 17:48.692
You're awake. That's good.
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

17:48.776 --> 17:50.986
(INHALES) This chamber,

17:51.069 --> 17:53.739
I created it
for experimenting on Dust.

17:53.822 --> 17:56.825
As such, it's lined
with adamantine,

17:56.909 --> 17:59.953
properties of which include
preventing Dust from escaping.

18:00.037 --> 18:04.708
Now you, as well as my daemon,
are entirely made of Dust.

18:04.792 --> 18:08.003
So you might find yourself
locked in here for eternity.

18:08.086 --> 18:09.797
ALARBUS: I am eternal.

18:09.880 --> 18:12.424
-I have no concept of time.
-Good for you.

18:12.508 --> 18:13.634
You'll be comfortable then.

18:13.717 --> 18:15.219
(SNIFFLES)
I'm going to begin now.

18:15.302 --> 18:16.637
I'm going to ask you
some questions

18:16.720 --> 18:17.930
and you will answer them.

18:18.013 --> 18:19.765
What's the Authority
so afraid of

18:19.848 --> 18:21.809
that he sent one angel
to attack another?

18:24.561 --> 18:26.230
Don't want to talk?

18:26.313 --> 18:29.483
Perhaps you are afraid
of revealing that the Authority

18:29.566 --> 18:31.819
no longer rules
in the Kingdom of Heaven,

18:31.902 --> 18:33.070
and that he has,
for some reason,

18:33.153 --> 18:34.321
appointed a regent?

18:34.404 --> 18:36.782
It's quite all right,
I already know.

18:36.865 --> 18:38.784
What's wrong with him
that he won't rule?

18:38.867 --> 18:40.869
Or is it that he can't? If he--

18:41.912 --> 18:46.500
(CHUCKLES)
Oh, now that's interesting.

18:46.583 --> 18:49.253
Now we're getting somewhere.
(SNIFFLES)

18:49.336 --> 18:51.380
Do you know
what else is interesting?

18:52.089 --> 18:54.800
Dust. Fascinating stuff.

18:54.883 --> 18:58.762
Spent most of my adult life
trying to understand it.

18:58.846 --> 19:01.306
And I once killed
an innocent young boy

19:02.558 --> 19:03.809
in order to harness it.

19:05.477 --> 19:08.856
But no one,
before this moment...

19:10.274 --> 19:13.360
has ever tried to weaponize it.

19:13.443 --> 19:15.737
-(THROTTLE CLANGS)
-(GRUNTS, SCREAMS)

19:15.821 --> 19:19.366
-(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)
-(ALARBUS GRUNTING)

19:24.746 --> 19:27.666
Enoch, brother of Baruch.

19:27.749 --> 19:31.128
-How did he become Regent?
-Do not dare use that name.

19:31.211 --> 19:32.796
-He is Metatron.
-(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

19:32.880 --> 19:34.798
ASRIEL: Metatron? Good.

19:34.882 --> 19:41.346
-(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)
-(ALARBUS GRUNTS)

19:41.430 --> 19:45.893
-Asriel, stop.
-(ALARBUS SCREAMING)

19:47.060 --> 19:49.271
-(GRUNTS)
-♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

19:49.354 --> 19:52.482
-What does he want?
-(GRUNTS) The end of this!

19:53.233 --> 19:56.820
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

19:56.904 --> 19:58.864
Dust is not
for you to understand.

20:00.741 --> 20:03.994
Conscious beings have become
dangerously independent.

20:04.077 --> 20:05.704
He will lead
a permanent inquisition

20:05.787 --> 20:08.040
into every world,
on every being.

20:08.123 --> 20:11.501
Until they understand
complete obedience.

20:11.585 --> 20:13.503
And with it, we will bring

20:13.587 --> 20:15.130
an end to the freedom
of thought and will,

20:15.213 --> 20:17.382
and control Dust
once and for all.

20:18.383 --> 20:20.385
How do I find him?

20:20.469 --> 20:23.221
ALARBUS: The Kingdom of Heaven
is not yours to enter.

20:24.348 --> 20:25.891
You think you're significant?

20:26.850 --> 20:28.560
He does not even know your name.

20:30.270 --> 20:31.647
Were he to notice you,

20:31.730 --> 20:33.899
he could crush you
and burn whatever remains.

20:36.193 --> 20:37.986
Doesn't even know my name.

20:40.948 --> 20:44.952
So this Metatron will require
a little more coaxing?

20:45.035 --> 20:48.455
And then, will his Kingdom come?

20:51.458 --> 20:54.044
Good. Very good.

20:54.127 --> 20:58.131
Wasn't so difficult, was it?
Didn't even take an eternity.

21:01.009 --> 21:05.764
-(DOOR SQUEAKS)
-(ALARBUS BREATHES HEAVILY)

21:10.936 --> 21:13.355
♪ (TENSE MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

21:13.438 --> 21:15.649
JOSEPH: Maddy's been here
for nine years.

21:15.732 --> 21:17.567
I joined a few years later.

21:17.651 --> 21:19.569
You've been on your own
all this time?

21:23.240 --> 21:25.200
We have a life in resistance.

21:26.618 --> 21:29.162
We can read, write, learn.

21:30.622 --> 21:33.166
All those things
are forbidden by the Temple.

21:33.250 --> 21:35.252
-Especially for...
-Girls.

21:39.298 --> 21:40.549
What about your parents?

21:44.386 --> 21:45.846
Our father stayed.

21:48.015 --> 21:49.057
He's one of them.

21:50.976 --> 21:53.270
When we ran away,
he helped us get out,

21:53.353 --> 21:54.688
but he wouldn't come.

21:55.439 --> 21:57.399
He wanted us to join the Temple.

21:58.859 --> 22:00.485
He thinks that
we'd let the Temple turn us

22:00.569 --> 22:02.237
into brain-dead followers.

22:02.946 --> 22:04.489
I'd rip their eyes out first.

22:04.573 --> 22:08.118
-(CHUCKLES) She actually would.
-Fair enough.

22:11.455 --> 22:13.040
So, where's everybody else gone?

22:13.123 --> 22:15.333
A stranger came here and...

22:16.293 --> 22:18.587
blew a hole in the sky.

22:18.670 --> 22:22.132
And then Commander Ogunwe
let everyone through it.

22:22.215 --> 22:24.092
Like a window...

22:24.176 --> 22:27.679
-to another world?
-Is that how you got here?

22:29.139 --> 22:30.599
Something like that, yes.

22:32.851 --> 22:34.352
And you decided not to go?

22:36.521 --> 22:39.775
We can't leave him, our father.

22:42.444 --> 22:44.362
I left my community once, too.

22:45.906 --> 22:47.157
Long time ago now.

22:48.366 --> 22:50.118
Left everything
I had ever known.

22:51.912 --> 22:53.914
It felt like the world
was ending.

22:56.249 --> 22:57.417
But now I can see,

22:57.501 --> 23:00.462
it was just beginning
to open up in front of me.

23:00.545 --> 23:03.006
Full of strangeness and mystery.

23:06.218 --> 23:07.260
I better go.

23:08.678 --> 23:09.930
Are you going to another world?

23:10.013 --> 23:11.598
MARY MALONE:
A few more, I think.

23:12.474 --> 23:14.101
I'm following these, um...

23:15.727 --> 23:19.147
sticks, they're telling me
where to go. (CHUCKLES)

23:19.231 --> 23:21.525
I know that sounds crazy,
so I won't--

23:21.608 --> 23:22.943
MADDY: Stay with us a while.

23:23.026 --> 23:25.654
Who knows when you'll next
have a chance to rest.

23:28.448 --> 23:29.449
Go on so.

23:31.409 --> 23:33.954
MADDY: Tell us more about why
you're looking for this girl.

23:35.539 --> 23:38.291
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

23:38.625 --> 23:39.709
Today...

23:41.044 --> 23:44.089
we have been offered
an opportunity.

23:46.091 --> 23:47.509
The opportunity...

23:48.885 --> 23:51.138
to purge this world...

23:54.558 --> 23:57.894
To purge these worlds...

23:59.813 --> 24:02.149
of all that has been
ailing them.

24:04.025 --> 24:10.574
We are going to release
the righteous from sin.

24:13.410 --> 24:16.663
Father Gomez will lead you,

24:16.746 --> 24:21.793
and the Authority will guide you
in your sacred mission.

24:23.003 --> 24:26.256
Be swift, be brutal.

24:27.048 --> 24:29.301
But make no mistake.

24:29.384 --> 24:34.264
The girl, Eve,
must not be allowed to escape.

24:35.098 --> 24:36.683
Retrieve the child.

24:38.310 --> 24:39.895
Retrieve the mother.

24:41.104 --> 24:42.981
Ad return them to me,

24:44.274 --> 24:45.650
dead or alive.

24:49.696 --> 24:52.073
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONCLUDES) ♪

25:11.384 --> 25:13.887
I understand that none of this
matters compared to him.

25:15.931 --> 25:18.141
I don't know
what else I'm supposed to do.

25:25.649 --> 25:28.610
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

25:30.987 --> 25:32.072
(SQUEAKS)

25:38.662 --> 25:40.372
(SIGHS)

26:07.524 --> 26:10.318
-(DOOR THUDS)
-(SIREN BLARING)

26:10.402 --> 26:14.155
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

26:40.765 --> 26:43.018
You know what this woman
is capable of.

26:43.101 --> 26:45.478
Balthamos and I
will take a closer look.

26:45.562 --> 26:48.356
You attract too much attention,
so stay here and keep watch.

26:49.190 --> 26:51.192
Do not underestimate her.

26:52.444 --> 26:53.445
I won't.

27:00.327 --> 27:02.912
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

27:13.381 --> 27:14.632
I'm not gonna hurt you.

27:15.884 --> 27:18.303
I-- I'm looking for a girl
on this island.

27:24.392 --> 27:26.353
Balthamos,
you're gonna scare her.

27:29.439 --> 27:31.900
Yes, angel.

27:33.485 --> 27:36.071
And this is Will.

27:41.326 --> 27:42.619
This is Ama.

27:46.456 --> 27:47.582
Ask her about Lyra.

27:49.834 --> 27:51.920
Is there a girl here?

27:56.257 --> 27:57.801
I care about her a lot.

28:01.888 --> 28:05.600
BALTHAMOS: There was a girl here
being kept asleep,

28:05.683 --> 28:07.727
by a woman
who claims to be her mother.

28:07.811 --> 28:10.939
But no mother
could possibly be so cruel.

28:11.940 --> 28:13.191
This mother would.

28:16.861 --> 28:18.279
Is that sun root?

28:20.907 --> 28:22.700
It's a waking medicine?

28:25.328 --> 28:28.123
Are you going to use that?

28:31.543 --> 28:32.585
Oh.

28:36.256 --> 28:39.968
The woman has gone,
but will be returning soon.

28:44.389 --> 28:45.515
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

28:55.442 --> 28:57.652
Stay here, okay?

28:57.735 --> 28:59.779
If you see her coming,
run and get help.

29:08.413 --> 29:11.875
(FIRE CRACKLES)

29:14.419 --> 29:16.921
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

29:23.928 --> 29:25.054
(WHISPERS) Lyra?

29:35.273 --> 29:37.317
MRS. COULTER: You see,
she's quite safe.

29:39.194 --> 29:40.778
WILL PARRY:
How did you get here?

29:40.862 --> 29:43.781
Oh. Uh, these chambers,
they have secrets.

29:45.658 --> 29:47.577
She's not safe,
you're drugging her!

29:48.328 --> 29:49.370
COULTER: Hmm.

29:50.705 --> 29:51.789
You've grown, Will.

29:53.416 --> 29:56.377
You know, I always suspected
you were coming,

29:56.461 --> 29:58.630
but I didn't think
you'd be the first.

30:01.007 --> 30:03.218
It's impressive.

30:03.301 --> 30:06.971
Why are you keeping her here?
Why won't you let her leave?

30:07.055 --> 30:09.599
-♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-Come.

30:10.808 --> 30:12.435
Let's sit. Hmm?

30:18.650 --> 30:20.276
Tea?

30:20.360 --> 30:22.195
Come on. I know for a fact
you have tea

30:22.278 --> 30:24.489
-in your world, too.
-Who else is coming?

30:27.408 --> 30:28.660
Did you bring the knife?

30:30.286 --> 30:32.580
(TEA POURING)

30:32.664 --> 30:33.831
May I see it?

30:35.291 --> 30:36.834
Why are you keeping her here?

30:39.837 --> 30:42.590
I am keeping her here
because I'm her mother,

30:43.341 --> 30:44.425
and I love her.

30:46.010 --> 30:47.762
Lyra's in the
most appalling danger,

30:47.845 --> 30:49.597
and here, I can keep her safe.

30:51.808 --> 30:53.434
(SIGHS) Please, sit down.

31:02.527 --> 31:04.529
What could be
more dangerous than you?

31:05.697 --> 31:06.739
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

31:08.157 --> 31:09.993
How sad
you can't see the truth.

31:12.287 --> 31:15.373
Three times
I have seen her in danger,

31:15.456 --> 31:18.084
and three times
I've tried to save her from it.

31:19.877 --> 31:21.296
It's cost me everything.

31:23.047 --> 31:24.716
And now she's in danger again.

31:26.050 --> 31:27.468
WILL: Who is she in danger from?

31:28.469 --> 31:29.846
The Magisterium.

31:32.390 --> 31:34.726
And they intend
to have her killed.

31:36.269 --> 31:38.605
Do you know
who they say she is, Will?

31:40.732 --> 31:42.150
I know there's a prophecy.

31:45.236 --> 31:46.904
They think she is Eve...

31:49.907 --> 31:51.451
the mother of all sin.

31:54.704 --> 31:56.873
And they think
she will do great damage.

31:58.875 --> 32:01.336
So they are determined
to murder her

32:01.419 --> 32:03.880
as an act of devotion.

32:06.382 --> 32:07.800
Unless we stop them.

32:10.428 --> 32:12.263
(INHALES SHARPLY)
Even if that's true,

32:13.097 --> 32:14.807
why are you keeping her asleep?

32:18.269 --> 32:19.771
'Cause she hates me, Will.

32:23.232 --> 32:24.984
And if I woke her, she'd run.

32:27.070 --> 32:28.905
In fact,
she's already tried to run.

32:31.491 --> 32:32.492
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

32:32.575 --> 32:35.495
So explain to her,
like you've explained to me.

32:35.578 --> 32:37.789
I am doing this
to keep her alive.

32:39.123 --> 32:41.334
Wouldn't your mother
do the same for you?

32:46.297 --> 32:47.799
A child needs their mother.

32:50.093 --> 32:51.469
You understand that, Will.

32:53.596 --> 32:54.764
You need your mother.

32:58.226 --> 33:00.311
And here's the trick
they never tell you.

33:01.479 --> 33:03.272
Your mother needs you.

33:06.192 --> 33:07.235
And that bond,

33:08.444 --> 33:09.654
it stretches,

33:10.655 --> 33:13.032
it transforms,
but it never breaks.

33:14.283 --> 33:15.284
Why?

33:17.453 --> 33:19.497
Because the line from here,

33:20.915 --> 33:21.999
to here...

33:23.459 --> 33:26.170
matters more
than any line in nature.

33:28.172 --> 33:29.173
It's primal.

33:30.591 --> 33:31.634
It's beautiful.

33:33.636 --> 33:36.305
It overwhelms
all other things...

33:41.602 --> 33:42.687
if you let it.

33:49.277 --> 33:50.278
Help me.

33:51.320 --> 33:54.323
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

33:56.200 --> 33:58.286
The three of us
could be extraordinary.

33:59.495 --> 34:01.748
Your strength, my guile,

34:01.831 --> 34:04.417
-Lyra's bravery--
-I'm not strong.

34:04.500 --> 34:07.170
You are strong, Will.
You think I can't see that?

34:13.634 --> 34:15.803
You promise
that you're keeping her safe?

34:17.388 --> 34:18.306
That you'll carry on

34:18.389 --> 34:20.516
-keeping her safe?
-I give you my word.

34:25.813 --> 34:27.690
Then I can leave her here.

34:27.774 --> 34:29.776
Go to Asriel,
like I was supposed to?

34:29.859 --> 34:34.989
No, no. No, no, no, no.
I-- I need you to stay.

34:35.072 --> 34:37.366
I saw what you did
at Carlo's house, we--

34:37.450 --> 34:39.076
we could help each other,
we could protect

34:39.160 --> 34:40.787
each other's vulnerabilities.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.706
Will, we can't stay here,
we have to keep moving.

34:43.790 --> 34:46.542
-You must come with us.
-I gave my word to my father

34:46.626 --> 34:48.169
that as soon as I knew
Lyra was safe,

34:48.252 --> 34:50.338
I would go to Asriel to fight.

34:52.340 --> 34:53.466
I have to do that.

34:53.549 --> 34:55.718
Do you-- do you understand
what you're doing?

34:56.427 --> 34:58.262
This-- (SIGHS)

34:58.346 --> 35:01.557
This is a betrayal bigger
than any I have committed.

35:04.393 --> 35:08.439
If you abandon us now,
you leave her for dead.

35:09.565 --> 35:11.108
Do you understand that?

35:14.320 --> 35:16.989
Thank you
for all you're doing for her.

35:19.200 --> 35:20.868
I'm gonna leave her
in your care.

35:25.456 --> 35:27.375
COULTER: Will, you're making
a mistake.

35:28.626 --> 35:29.710
You--

35:38.511 --> 35:39.762
I thought he'd stay.

35:45.810 --> 35:48.020
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

35:49.772 --> 35:51.482
ASRIEL: We're going
to find that knife

35:51.566 --> 35:53.734
and we're going to use it
to destroy Metatron.

35:53.818 --> 35:56.195
You know nothing of him.

35:56.279 --> 35:58.781
He is the dark angel,
you cannot fight.

35:58.865 --> 36:00.741
LORD ASRIEL:
I can because I must.

36:00.825 --> 36:03.119
Ruta, this knife,
it's the weapon

36:03.202 --> 36:04.787
you heard the cliff-ghasts
talking about?

36:04.871 --> 36:06.205
AEsahaettr. Yes.

36:06.289 --> 36:08.457
Though I wasn't aware
it required a bearer.

36:08.541 --> 36:11.043
Or that it would have been
the boy who was with Lyra.

36:11.127 --> 36:13.588
So, we find Lyra,
we find the boy.

36:13.671 --> 36:14.964
RUTA: I have seen them together.

36:15.047 --> 36:17.008
Where one goes,
the other follows.

36:17.091 --> 36:20.052
Who is this girl that everyone
is so interested in?

36:20.136 --> 36:21.429
RUTA: Asriel's daughter.

36:22.430 --> 36:24.515
They believe she is Eve.

36:24.599 --> 36:26.142
-Eve?
-LORD ASRIEL: Hmm.

36:26.225 --> 36:27.518
OGUNWE: Who is Eve?

36:27.602 --> 36:30.605
RUTA: In some worlds,
the mother of all sin.

36:30.688 --> 36:32.940
OGUNWE: Your daughter
is the mother of all sin?

36:33.024 --> 36:34.609
(SIGHS) They believe so.

36:34.692 --> 36:36.903
But they believe a great deal
of fanciful nonsense.

36:36.986 --> 36:39.405
And you didn't think
it worth mentioning before?

36:39.488 --> 36:41.657
-Where is she?
-We don't know.

36:41.741 --> 36:43.409
OGUNWE:
Then how will we protect her?

36:43.492 --> 36:44.785
(CHUCKLES)

36:44.869 --> 36:46.495
If there's one girl
in all the worlds

36:46.579 --> 36:49.582
that doesn't need protecting,
it is Lyra.

36:49.665 --> 36:51.959
Now, what I need is that knife.

36:52.043 --> 36:53.920
The Magisterium
can help us in this matter.

36:54.003 --> 36:56.088
Roke, I want you
to contact Salmakia.

36:56.172 --> 36:59.050
Once she knows where Lyra is,
I'll follow her there.

36:59.133 --> 37:01.385
You will use
your own daughter as a trap?

37:01.469 --> 37:03.054
I have already risked
everything I have

37:03.137 --> 37:04.263
to get us this far.

37:04.347 --> 37:05.806
My fortune, my reputation.

37:05.890 --> 37:08.935
But what we risk now, here,
in the next few weeks,

37:09.018 --> 37:11.395
that will shape the course
of history forever.

37:11.479 --> 37:13.981
So if I have to journey
to every world, I will.

37:14.065 --> 37:16.859
If I have to
incarcerate every angel, I will.

37:16.943 --> 37:17.944
If I have to take a knife

37:18.027 --> 37:20.488
to the heart of the Authority
himself, I will.

37:20.571 --> 37:24.283
And yes, I will risk Lyra,
I will risk my own daughter

37:24.367 --> 37:26.285
because the alternative,
Commander,

37:26.369 --> 37:28.412
is what happened to yours.

37:28.496 --> 37:31.916
And I would risk everything
and everyone

37:31.999 --> 37:34.877
to ensure
that can never happen again.

37:35.836 --> 37:38.631
So I suggest
you all ask yourselves,

37:38.714 --> 37:40.925
what are you willing to risk?

37:41.008 --> 37:43.135
An angel has been killed
and all you can think about

37:43.219 --> 37:44.387
is how that might benefit you.

37:44.470 --> 37:46.806
Would you rather
he die in vain?

37:53.604 --> 37:55.982
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:56.065 --> 37:59.318
Xaphania, the great betrayer.

38:02.697 --> 38:04.949
You are consorting
with humans now?

38:06.283 --> 38:09.286
Was a millennia in exile not
degradation enough for you?

38:10.204 --> 38:12.665
You speak of betrayal

38:12.748 --> 38:17.128
when you have taken orders
to kill one of our own kind?

38:17.211 --> 38:22.216
Baruch is-- was
an enemy of the Kingdom.

38:24.218 --> 38:26.387
(CHUCKLES)

38:26.470 --> 38:29.390
What few rebels there are
will not fight for you.

38:30.349 --> 38:31.600
They are defectors.

38:31.684 --> 38:33.519
They run away from conflict,
not towards it.

38:33.602 --> 38:35.980
They will fight
for what they believe in.

38:37.148 --> 38:39.400
Why have you really come
to see me?

38:41.569 --> 38:43.946
Perhaps, you wanted to see
if it is true

38:44.947 --> 38:46.991
what Asriel
has been doing to me?

38:50.661 --> 38:52.872
Don't expect your rebels
to follow a mortal

38:52.955 --> 38:55.875
who enjoys torturing angels.

38:55.958 --> 38:58.711
Where is the Authority?

39:01.005 --> 39:03.382
Hiding behind a Regent
who cares for nothing,

39:03.466 --> 39:05.009
but his own greatness?

39:08.637 --> 39:12.183
The Kingdom, as we know it,
has already gone, Alarbus.

39:12.975 --> 39:15.269
This is our final rebellion.

39:23.277 --> 39:24.862
♪ (TENSE MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

39:28.991 --> 39:32.244
-BALTHAMOS: What happened?
-She's a liar.

39:32.328 --> 39:35.414
-And yet, you're drawn to her.
-WILL: I know what I'm doing.

39:35.498 --> 39:38.000
-(AIRCRAFT WHIRRING)
-Look.

39:41.545 --> 39:44.340
There is no time now.
This is absurd.

39:44.423 --> 39:46.550
Baruch died for a purpose,
but this...

39:48.177 --> 39:51.972
-this is meaningless.
-I promise it will work.

39:52.056 --> 39:55.142
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

39:55.226 --> 39:57.144
(RADIO STATIC)

39:57.228 --> 39:59.230
PILOT: Five minutes
to destination.

40:09.031 --> 40:10.741
(STATIC SQUEAKS)

40:12.701 --> 40:13.702
What is this?

40:13.786 --> 40:15.287
It's kind of a Dust beam
communication device.

40:15.371 --> 40:18.457
We have a message from our agent
in the Magisterium.

40:18.541 --> 40:19.959
Load stan resonating, go ahead.

40:20.042 --> 40:22.128
SALMAKIA: Lyra is with a woman
named Marisa Coulter.

40:24.630 --> 40:26.465
Of course, she is.
How close are they?

40:26.549 --> 40:28.509
LADY SALMAKIA:
We are about to land
on a remote island

40:28.592 --> 40:30.386
in the German Ocean. Fairisle.

40:31.345 --> 40:32.805
I know the place.

40:32.888 --> 40:35.724
I'll take the Intention Craft,
it's the fastest way.

40:35.808 --> 40:37.476
Agent Salmakia,
get to the children,

40:37.560 --> 40:39.228
get them to safety,
away from the woman,

40:39.311 --> 40:41.564
and then stay with them
until I arrive. Understood?

40:41.647 --> 40:44.567
-SALMAKIA: Understood.
-You will go?

40:44.650 --> 40:47.486
I must. You heard
what the angel said.

40:47.570 --> 40:50.823
AEsahaettr, God destroyer.

40:50.906 --> 40:51.949
Hmm.

40:53.826 --> 40:55.161
In which case,

40:56.620 --> 40:58.038
try not to die.

40:58.581 --> 40:59.665
(CHUCKLES)

41:07.923 --> 41:10.217
The child is asking
what you are doing?

41:11.051 --> 41:13.220
I'm counting my steps.

41:13.304 --> 41:15.306
We'll return by them
in another world.

41:27.651 --> 41:28.819
(GUN COCKS)

41:32.114 --> 41:35.534
-(HYDRAULIC PRESSURE HISSING)
-(DOOR THUDDING)

41:35.618 --> 41:37.995
(GRUNTS)

41:44.418 --> 41:45.961
(GOLDEN MONKEY GIBBERING)

41:50.841 --> 41:55.346
(AIRCRAFT SIREN BLARING)

41:58.182 --> 42:01.435
Oh, no, no, no. No, no, no, no.

42:12.321 --> 42:17.451
-(INTENTION CRAFT RATTLES)
-(ENGINE STALLS)

42:17.534 --> 42:20.579
The Intention Craft
works through clarity.

42:20.663 --> 42:22.164
Your mind is muddled.

42:22.248 --> 42:26.627
(INHALES) I know exactly what
and who we're going for.

42:26.710 --> 42:32.883
-(BREATHES DEEPLY)
-(INTENTION CRAFT WHIRRING)

42:36.470 --> 42:39.181
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

42:57.700 --> 42:58.951
(COULTER GASPS)

43:03.414 --> 43:04.581
(GRUNTS)

43:14.258 --> 43:15.426
Do your worst.

43:26.270 --> 43:27.980
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

43:28.063 --> 43:29.189
WILL: As soon as I've got her,

43:29.273 --> 43:30.983
I'll come back through
and close the window.

43:31.066 --> 43:32.526
I need you to keep watch.

43:32.609 --> 43:34.653
BALTHAMOS: I'm sorry, Will.
I must leave.

43:35.070 --> 43:36.155
Balthamos!

43:36.238 --> 43:37.698
BALTHAMOS: It was one thing
for the AEsahaettr,

43:37.781 --> 43:40.576
but this,
this is a human matter.

43:40.659 --> 43:43.495
Don't go. I know
this is hard for you,

43:43.579 --> 43:45.331
but I need you to trust me.

43:45.414 --> 43:49.209
I can't. I'm sorry.
Not for this.

43:49.293 --> 43:51.545
-WILL: Balthamos!
-(BALTHAMOS SWOOSHES)

43:51.628 --> 43:54.006
♪ (MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:07.978 --> 44:12.149
(CHUCKLES) Thank you.
But go home, okay?

44:12.941 --> 44:14.318
Stay out of danger.

44:20.699 --> 44:23.243
(MAGICAL SWOOSH)

44:28.207 --> 44:31.251
(AIRCRAFT WHIRRING)

44:38.634 --> 44:42.596
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:58.320 --> 45:01.031
(INTENTION CRAFT WHIRRING)

45:06.829 --> 45:09.456
♪ (TENSE MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

45:20.050 --> 45:21.176
Mrs. Coulter?

45:24.847 --> 45:25.931
That's me.

45:28.350 --> 45:29.726
You're too late, Father.

45:30.894 --> 45:31.979
She's gone.

45:34.231 --> 45:36.108
A boy got here first.

45:37.609 --> 45:40.112
You know, he had
several hundred miles

45:40.195 --> 45:42.281
and the boundaries
between worlds to cross.

45:42.364 --> 45:43.490
And yet...

45:44.867 --> 45:47.369
still managed
to get here before you.

45:48.203 --> 45:49.872
(CHUCKLES) Bravo.

45:53.292 --> 45:56.044
But I don't know
why I'm surprised.

45:56.128 --> 45:58.505
MacPhail likes to think
he knows what he's doing,

45:58.589 --> 46:02.176
but he prevaricates.
Dithers. Don't you think?

46:07.598 --> 46:08.849
(GROANS)

46:13.604 --> 46:14.897
That was from the boy.

46:16.356 --> 46:18.525
Surprisingly vicious
little brat.

46:31.330 --> 46:33.916
I am going
to take Lyra now, Mrs. Coulter.

46:35.417 --> 46:38.504
And I'd rather not travel back
to Geneva after nightfall.

46:41.882 --> 46:42.925
Like I said...

46:44.676 --> 46:45.719
she's not here.

46:51.892 --> 46:52.893
Please.

46:56.980 --> 47:01.777
I'm sorry. Her fate was decided
long before I arrived here.

47:10.244 --> 47:11.328
(CLICKS TONGUE) Okay.

47:23.173 --> 47:25.884
(FIRE CRACKLING)

47:34.434 --> 47:35.519
She's in there.

47:36.853 --> 47:37.896
Sit.

47:42.526 --> 47:44.736
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

47:53.453 --> 47:54.746
What was your plan?

47:56.456 --> 47:58.792
Would you have
kept her unconscious forever?

48:00.252 --> 48:02.421
Run from world to world,

48:02.504 --> 48:04.464
trying to escape
the alethiometer?

48:05.882 --> 48:09.970
Forever? You are not stupid.

48:10.053 --> 48:13.557
Quite the opposite. You knew
we would find her, eventually.

48:15.559 --> 48:16.768
And destroy her.

48:19.104 --> 48:20.772
That is her destiny.

48:23.525 --> 48:26.111
You brought this fate upon her.

48:26.194 --> 48:29.114
You gave her the terrible
punishment of her existence.

48:30.407 --> 48:31.450
And now, when she reaches

48:31.533 --> 48:33.910
the hands
of Father President MacPhail...

48:36.330 --> 48:37.331
death.

48:41.752 --> 48:42.753
(GASPS)

48:48.467 --> 48:50.302
-(GRUNTS)
-Why have you been

48:50.385 --> 48:53.055
prolonging her pain in this way?

48:55.349 --> 48:56.475
I don't know.

49:01.063 --> 49:02.022
I'm sorry.

49:08.904 --> 49:14.201
-(SHARP HISSING)
-(WIND BLOWING)

49:14.951 --> 49:19.790
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

49:23.960 --> 49:26.254
I did not know
what else to do, Father.

49:28.215 --> 49:30.342
(SCOFFS) That is not true.

49:38.308 --> 49:40.727
The answer was so simple
and you knew it...

49:42.938 --> 49:43.939
all along.

50:00.330 --> 50:03.375
A truly loving act
would have been to let her die.

50:08.588 --> 50:12.467
To drift off in a sleep so deep
that no one could ever hurt her.

50:15.887 --> 50:17.347
In her mother's arms.

50:29.860 --> 50:31.945
It is time for you
to let her go now.

50:35.073 --> 50:36.283
To kill one's own child

50:36.366 --> 50:39.244
takes a kind of strength
I do not possess.

50:40.162 --> 50:41.496
Oh, but you do.

50:43.707 --> 50:45.917
You have greater strength
than you know.

50:50.505 --> 50:51.882
Do it for me, please.

50:54.551 --> 50:55.761
Grant me that.

51:08.064 --> 51:09.941
(WHISPERS) Hey!
Hey, we're leaving.

51:11.902 --> 51:13.028
COULTER: Please.

51:16.698 --> 51:17.908
(GROWLS)

51:22.579 --> 51:26.166
(SNARLS, SCREECHES)

51:26.249 --> 51:29.419
-(FATHER GOMEZ GRUNTING)
-(BREATHES HEAVILY)

51:29.503 --> 51:34.049
Oh, dear. Perhaps you were right
about that strength.

51:36.760 --> 51:39.888
You came back for us.
I knew you would, Will.

51:39.971 --> 51:41.848
(BREATHES HEAVILY)
What are you doing?

51:42.808 --> 51:43.725
We're leaving.

51:43.809 --> 51:45.352
COULTER:
Well, I'll come with you.

51:47.646 --> 51:50.649
We'll be safer together.
You need the two of us-- No, no.

51:50.732 --> 51:54.110
-(KNIFE HISSES SHARPLY)
-(BREATHES HEAVILY)

51:54.569 --> 51:55.612
Stay back.

51:58.240 --> 51:59.741
You're not coming with us.

52:03.662 --> 52:05.121
She needs me, Will.

52:08.250 --> 52:10.252
Please, don't take her from me.

52:12.796 --> 52:14.506
-Please.
-Ju-- just stay back.

52:16.466 --> 52:18.552
COULTER: Will?

52:18.635 --> 52:21.054
Do you think it's that easy
to dispose of me?

52:21.137 --> 52:22.055
Get away from us.

52:22.138 --> 52:23.890
COULTER: Is that
what you do, Will?

52:25.851 --> 52:29.020
Was your mother
as easily disposed of?

52:29.104 --> 52:30.605
Why did you leave her?

52:40.866 --> 52:46.830
(SHARP HISSING)

52:46.913 --> 52:48.248
Where is she, Will?

52:53.169 --> 52:54.379
Where is your mother?

53:01.303 --> 53:02.470
Look at me, Will.

53:07.017 --> 53:08.059
Look at me.

53:10.020 --> 53:11.187
Look at me.

53:14.274 --> 53:17.611
(KNIFE CLANGS, SHATTERS)

53:21.740 --> 53:22.824
What have you done?

53:22.908 --> 53:26.369
(BREATHES HEAVILY)
What have you done?

53:27.412 --> 53:28.788
WILL: You broke the knife.

53:30.874 --> 53:33.209
(GOLDEN MONKEY GIBBERS)

53:37.088 --> 53:40.383
Leave. (PANTS)

53:40.467 --> 53:43.178
Without the knife,
you're useless to me.

53:43.261 --> 53:44.638
Please, leave now, Will.

53:46.973 --> 53:48.099
Leave!

53:49.935 --> 53:54.564
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

53:57.776 --> 54:00.612
Lyra, move, move, move.

54:00.695 --> 54:05.325
♪ (MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

54:07.702 --> 54:09.955
Don't look at me
like that, please.

54:11.998 --> 54:12.999
Let me go.

54:16.670 --> 54:18.046
Please, let me go.

54:21.716 --> 54:23.551
-(WINGS FLUTTERING)
-(STING CLANGING)

54:24.219 --> 54:26.513
(WINGS FLUTTERING)

54:26.596 --> 54:29.933
It was only a small sting.
She'll be fine in a few hours.

54:33.019 --> 54:35.897
-Boy, do you have the knife?
-Who are you?

54:35.981 --> 54:38.692
SALMAKIA: I'm under instruction
to take you to Asriel.

54:38.775 --> 54:40.568
-Follow me.
-LYRA: No.

54:40.652 --> 54:42.070
No, we're not going to Asriel.

54:42.153 --> 54:45.865
-It's okay. Come on.
-This is a way out.

55:01.214 --> 55:03.091
-(GUNSHOTS)
-WILL: Whoa! (GRUNTS)

55:03.550 --> 55:04.634
Get down.

55:04.718 --> 55:10.932
-(IOREK BYRNISON ROARS)
-(SOLDIERS GRUNT)

55:11.016 --> 55:13.476
-Iorek's here?
-I'll explain later.

55:14.519 --> 55:19.607
-(GUNSHOTS)
-(ROARS)

55:23.486 --> 55:26.990
-(ROARS)
-(SOLDIER GRUNTS, SCREAMS)

55:27.073 --> 55:33.747
(ROARS)

55:34.372 --> 55:35.415
(WILL EXCLAIMS)

55:37.500 --> 55:38.793
Get her out of here!

55:38.877 --> 55:41.087
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

55:42.922 --> 55:46.009
-(PANTS)
-(GUN COCKS)

55:47.510 --> 55:49.554
(BOTH GRUNT)

55:50.513 --> 55:51.514
(GUNSHOT)

55:55.185 --> 55:56.603
Hey! You okay?

56:04.486 --> 56:05.737
Will, we need to go.

56:07.072 --> 56:08.073
Come on.

56:11.326 --> 56:14.871
(PANTS)

56:16.331 --> 56:17.540
Come with us.

56:22.879 --> 56:23.880
Thank you.

56:27.008 --> 56:28.009
Come on.

56:33.890 --> 56:36.518
(PANTS)

56:36.601 --> 56:40.897
(WINGS FLUTTER)

56:50.198 --> 56:52.909
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

56:52.992 --> 56:56.371
(INTENTION CRAFT RUMBLES)

57:06.005 --> 57:07.006
Lyra?

57:09.676 --> 57:10.677
Lyra?

57:24.232 --> 57:28.778
(GROWLS) We're too late.

57:33.032 --> 57:34.159
Damn.

57:38.538 --> 57:42.458
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC TURNS HOPEFUL) ♪

58:11.654 --> 58:14.490
♪ (HOPEFUL MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

58:14.574 --> 58:18.786
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

59:27.981 --> 59:32.026
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
